The paper focuses on the intersection of big data and privacy, with a particular emphasis on the security of informational assets. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the category of "Computer Science and Game Theory" (cs.GT) or "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). However, the paper also performs a systematic literature review and uses bibliometrics and text mining analysis, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of "Databases" (cs.DB) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of TOPSIS and VIKOR ranks, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the legal and regulatory aspects of big data privacy, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of "Computers and Society" (cs.CY).
